Research suggests those who are thought to look most average and most attractive, due to lack of oddities.

'Average faces are more attractive, likely due to the averaging out of unattractive idiosyncrasies,' says Drew Walker, a psychological scientist.

He carried out the study alongside Edward Vul of the University of California, San Diego.

Their findings were published in Psychological Science, a journal of the Association for Psychological Science, reported Science Daily.

'Perhaps it's like Tolstoy's families: Beautiful people are all alike, but every unattractive person is unattractive in their own way,' says Walker.

